    "stem": {
      "content": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "strong": true,
              "text": "Research Question: "
            },
            {
              "text": "What is the combined effect of medication and diet on blood pressure in adult males?"
            }
          ],
          "id": "pu0e3gkt9iaja2t",
          "type": "p"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "A randomized, controlled experiment investigated this question using a random sample of 540 adult males as subjects. At the beginning of the study, researchers measured the blood pressure of all the subjects. Each subject was given a month's supply of either Drug A, Drug B, or a placebo, then was assigned to be on either a low-fat diet or a low-salt diet for that month-long period. At the end of the month, the researchers measured the blood pressure of each subject again, and compared the two blood pressure readings. "
            }
          ],
          "id": "lvmc6f0i814fau7",
          "type": "p"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Which of the following is an explanatory variable in this study? Check all that apply."
            }
          ],
